From the ensemble averaged SCG and BCG signals, three instantaneous kinetic energies (K) transmitted to the sensors by the cardiac activity were computed based on each subject’s inertial parameters (body mass for the linear channels; matrix of inertia for the rotational channels, as estimated using a model based on the height and weight of the subject28): namely (a) the linear BCG kinetic energy (regrouping x, y, and z), (b) the rotational BCG kinetic energy (regrouping x, y, and z), and (c) the SCG kinetic energy along the linear z axis. These computations gave the following ensemble-averaged signals: \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
