The evolution of the cardiovascular status in 22 participants was longitudinally assessed during a HDBR study with a HDT duration of 60 days by using novel metrics extracted through a PCM system that combined ECG, SCG, and BCG measurements. Several PCM metrics have been found to be affected by long-duration exposure to HDT and to expose changes that correlate with the simultaneous decrements in SV and VO2 max. Since a positive effect of the countermeasure was shown for SV and VO2 max, this effect was then also visible on some PCM metrics and in particular \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
